üêß Linux Basic Commands (Cheat Sheet)

1. File & Directory Commands

| Task                        | Command                            |
| --------------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| List files                  | `ls`                               |
| List all (including hidden) | `ls -a`                            |
| Long listing with details   | `ls -l`                            |
| Change directory            | `cd /path/to/dir`                  |
| Go back one directory       | `cd ..`                            |
| Create a directory          | `mkdir folder_name`                |
| Create empty file           | `touch file.txt`                   |
| Copy file                   | `cp source.txt dest.txt`           |
| Move/rename file            | `mv old.txt new.txt`               |
| Delete file                 | `rm file.txt`                      |
| Delete folder recursively   | `rm -r folder_name`                |
| View file content           | `cat file.txt`                     |
| View file page by page      | `less file.txt` or `more file.txt` |
| Search inside file          | `grep "text" file.txt`             |

---

2. File Permissions & Ownership

| Task               | Command                                |
| ------------------ | -------------------------------------- |
| View permissions   | `ls -l`                                |
| Change permissions | `chmod +x file.sh` *(make executable)* |
| Change owner       | `chown user file.txt`                  |
| Change group       | `chgrp group file.txt`                 |

---

3. User & Group Management

| Task               | Command                |
| ------------------ | ---------------------- |
| Add user           | `sudo adduser newuser` |
| Switch user        | `su - username`        |
| Check current user | `whoami`               |
| Show user info     | `id`                   |
| List users         | `cat /etc/passwd`      |

---

4. Process & System Monitoring

| Task                        | Command         |
| --------------------------- | --------------- |
| Running processes           | `ps aux`        |
| Interactive process monitor | `top` or `htop` |
| Kill process                | `kill PID`      |
| System uptime               | `uptime`        |
| Disk usage                  | `df -h`         |
| Memory usage                | `free -h`       |

---

5. Package Management (Debian/Ubuntu)

| Task                | Command                        |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| Update package list | `sudo apt update`              |
| Upgrade packages    | `sudo apt upgrade`             |
| Install package     | `sudo apt install packagename` |
| Remove package      | `sudo apt remove packagename`  |

---

6. Networking

| Task             | Command                       |
| ---------------- | ----------------------------- |
| Show IP address  | `ip a` or `ifconfig`          |
| Ping a server    | `ping google.com`             |
| DNS lookup       | `nslookup domain.com`         |
| Download file    | `wget URL`                    |
| Check open ports | `netstat -tuln` or `ss -tuln` |

---

7. SSH (Secure Shell)

| Task                     | Command                         |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------- |
| Connect to remote server | `ssh username@ip_address`       |
| Use custom port          | `ssh -p 2222 user@ip`           |
| Copy file to server      | `scp file.txt user@ip:/path`    |
| Copy file from server    | `scp user@ip:/path/file.txt ./` |
| Generate SSH key pair    | `ssh-keygen`                    |
| Add SSH key to agent     | `ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_rsa`         |

---

8. Bash Shortcuts 

| Task                 | Command    |
| -------------------- | ---------- |
| Repeat last command  | `!!`       |
| History of commands  | `history`  |
| Auto-complete        | `<Tab>`    |
| Stop current command | `Ctrl + C` |
| Clear screen         | `clear`    |

---

9. Logs & Services

| Task              | Command                       |
| ----------------- | ----------------------------- |
| View system log   | `cat /var/log/syslog`         |
| Start service     | `sudo systemctl start nginx`  |
| Stop service      | `sudo systemctl stop nginx`   |
| Enable on boot    | `sudo systemctl enable nginx` |
| Status of service | `systemctl status nginx`      |
